Human rights activist and Senator who represented Kaduna central senatorial district in the 8th National Assembly, Senator Shehu Sani said the Federal government has failed in providing enough palliatives to sustain the lockdown, hence taking a dangerous gamble of opening the gate in Abuja on Monday 4th. This is just as he also averred that the Federal government has also failed to conduct enough tests and therefore left with no option but to allow people to fend for themselves. Senator Sani who bared his mind on his verified Facebook account said, once the offices and businesses are opened, nobody will listen to conditions attached to it again, stressing that it is either there is lockdown or no lockdown. According to him, “the Covid19 Billions is still with the CBN, the PTF are tired of wearing face masks, talking to the media and holding the keys of the gate; they have decided to take a dangerous gamble by opening the gate in Abuja on Monday. “Once the offices and businesses are opened, nobody will listen to any grammar of conditions attached to it. Its either there is Lockdown or no lockdown. “The FG has failed to provide enough palliatives to sustain the Lockdown and unable to conduct enough tests and now let the people out to fend for themselves” he stated. 